1. d4 {In an encounter in which you easily could think that black (Richard
Rapport a usual member of 2700 club) played a what one can consider a coffeehouse attack and got an inferior position against solid Alexader Riazantsev.
Nevertheless, the Russian went astray and the game was almost a draw when he
made another blunder and lost almost immediately. It was a hardly seen blunder in top
level tournament of this kind.} e6 2. c4 f5 {The time to consider Dutch/
